<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,1093,1229]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[248,464,1093,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Rhaphium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[248,464,1093,1119]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Rhaphium micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is a new species group containing species with a triangular postpedicel (first flagellomere), at most 2.5 × as long as wide, with arista longer than postpedicel (1.5 to 3 ×), 5 dc and long flattened cerci (nearly twice as long as epandrium), combined with in lateral view short rounded surstyli and a twisted short, but erect hypandrium.
</paragraph>
